                <head>Comments</head>
                <p xml:id="KR2a0001-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-10a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-07-30T20:38:46.873+09:00">First variation of "美", but not recognized in the translation.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-12a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-01T05:58:22.917+09:00">慎以 not 慎於! [TW]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-14a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-01T23:56:48.244+09:00">Interesting: 自免於</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-14a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-01T23:57:12.004+09:00">萃於</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-15a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-02T00:08:50.531+09:00">One of the few places where a direct insight into the inner emotional life is granted.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-23a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-05T23:20:27.918+09:00">Translation deviates considerably from original syntax.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-32a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-12T00:29:14.276+09:00">以……說……</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-40a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-14T20:11:26.121+09:00">The syntactical structure is obviously quite different here, the "human heart" is actually more closely discussed here. It is as if here the heart guides the person. [TW]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_031-40a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-14T20:14:37.667+09:00">After this, one part is missing.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_032-17a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-29T03:15:16.956+09:00">Doesn't zhi here refer to the whole matter rather than to a person? [TW]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_032-20a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-29T03:25:11.603+09:00">絀 hier als vttoN1. N2?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_032-26a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-08-30T03:09:18.307+09:00">Translation deviates syntactically considerably from the original.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_032-33a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-09-04T02:54:31.772+09:00">亂 = nab.post-N political disarray caused by N?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_032-33a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-09-04T02:57:00.293+09:00">城 iussive!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_032-61a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-09-17T23:10:09.249+09:00">This translation is rather odd.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_032-64a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-09-18T22:57:05.569+09:00">茀 -&gt; 孛, a tailless comet</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2a0001_tls_033-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2022-10-16T01:54:15.867+09:00">徐廣: “古書‘穆’字多作‘繆’。”</seg>
                </p>
